<br>
Now I know some of you are going to throw down on this topic, but it wasn't so bad with Mage/Necro charm as some people think/thought.  Why? Well yes necro's can FD so the risk was fairly low... But Agro kiting for them is more efficent and has nearly no risk. <br>
<br>
Mages can Charm what? In BoT, and the Hole (And Saryrn fight I guess)... few other fights where bosses summon pets.  But how is it over powering for a mage? we have no slow vs summoned... nor snare.  Soloing was possible but risky... and all the charm did was bring back the ability for us to duo well.<br>
<br>
SoE, I assume you are doing this because Mages and Ench's can pretty much solo/duo a mini that can drop runes.  Well instead of nerfing a spell that has such a limited use anyway (for mages)... make the mini's unslowable.  At least that keeps people from 3 boxing there way a rune instead of soloing it... they might need a full group or two.<br>
<br>
I think I'll make another thread tomorrow about this... mostly listing other ways to tone it down without completely ripping away it's usefulness.  Just off the top of my head I could list a dozen things that would tone it down nicely... &gt;. <p><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://home.attbi.com/~hunterx/damlyn.jpg"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--><br>
