<br>
HAHAHAHAHAHAHA sweet irony!<br>
<br>
Did you seriously expect that only enchanter charm would be touched? The reality is, though this will hurt ench charm soloing to a degree, a lot of enchanters never actually hasted their pets. I'm one that hastes, but there are several ways of upping a mob's DPS through other means if I really need to. Mages though get hurt a lot more since they could haste their charmed pets by quite a bit more then ench.<br>
<br>
The change to -10MR will also hurt, though definitly less for enchanter then other classes. It means I will no longer be assured of charm landing on the first try without tash. Charm breaks will be more frequent, but the difference with the current CoD at MR -50 with or without tash is negligeable when you have TD3 and that our max duration is pretty short anyways. Again, the MR change will be much more noticable to other classes. Not to mention for instance that the mage charm's max duration just got lowered by quite a bit.<br>
<br>
In the end the nerf means I will no longer be able to solo an aa every 30min (hypotetically of course), and will change it to around 45min considering no haste or more possible charm breaks. It can be lowered if I use other DPS enhancing methods. I will also no longer be able to solo some named mobs like a greater corrupted pusling as it required your pet to have haste to outmatch it (however duo is very doable). Charm breaks will be a bit more frequent, but since the pet is no longer hasted, there is much less risk on the charm break. DPS will be significantly lower, but again that's the only number that damage dealers ever cared about right? Am I happy about the nerf? Heck no. But it is manageable. A number of enchanters won't even feel it since they don't haste. The use of it in groups is still quite strong, and soloing while slower is still doable. This will actually hurt mages more then it will enchanters in the solo department.<br>
<br>
So congratulations, you have succeeded in nerfing the enchanter charm after lots of whining, angered the enchanter community, proved that the mage community is the whiniest class community around with it's constant CoD nerf threads(move over druids), and still ended up nerfing yourselfs in the process. The crybabies got their pacifiers to suck on, but got a diaper rash in the process. So here's a toast<!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> . <br>
